WEBVTT

00:04.371 --> 00:05.339 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.372 --> 00:06.340 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.373 --> 00:07.641 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ALISON STEWART: And I'm Alison
Stewart.

00:07.674 --> 00:10.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: On the "NewsHour"
tonight:
off to a rocky start.

00:10.344 --> 00:14.948 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Republican-controlled
Congress opens the
new session with a fight over
ethics.

00:14.982 --> 00:19.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALISON STEWART: Also ahead this
Tuesday, Judy
sits down for the first part of
an interview

00:19.620 --> 00:24.291 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with CIA Director John Brennan
to talk about
Russia, hacking and more.

00:24.324 --> 00:30.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN BRENNAN, CIA Director:
There are so many
ways to get into the digital
domain right

00:30.130 --> 00:31.999 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
now and to collect information.

00:32.032 --> 00:35.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's one of the things that
we, as a country,
I don't think, have come to
terms with, just

00:35.702 --> 00:38.405 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
how vulnerable we are.

00:38.438 --> 00:44.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And caught in the
aftermath
of Turkey's failed coup,
soldiers flee their

00:44.678 --> 00:48.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
homeland, while the president
demands their
return.

00:48.181 --> 00:52.786 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Turkey's
President Erdogan
has been ramping up the rhetoric
in relation

00:52.819 --> 00:56.423 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the military personnel
accused of complicity
in the coup.

00:56.456 --> 01:02.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Erdogan has said it is simply
inexcusable
to give shelter to people he
calls terrorist

01:02.262 --> 01:03.563 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
soldiers.

01:03.597 --> 01:10.737 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALISON STEWART: All that and
more on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:10.771 --> 01:13.573 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:13.607 --> 01:21.548 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening, and
happy new
year.

01:21.581 --> 01:25.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're going to be having some
guests joining
me here at the "NewsHour" anchor
desk in the

01:25.886 --> 01:27.754 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
coming weeks.

01:27.788 --> 01:31.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, it's Alison Stewart,
who many of
you will recognize from the
weekend "NewsHour."

01:31.491 --> 01:32.459 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Welcome, Alison.

01:32.492 --> 01:34.328 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ALISON STEWART: Well, thank you,
Judy.

01:34.361 --> 01:39.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, in our lead
story tonight:
The 115th Congress is officially
off and running,

01:39.566 --> 01:43.570 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but House Republicans stumbled
out of the
gate on this opening day.

01:43.603 --> 01:45.639 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins begins our
coverage.

01:45.672 --> 01:50.844 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: For
Republicans, day one
of Congress and what they hope
is a bright

01:50.877 --> 01:55.916 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
now era for their party started
with old issues
of internal dispute.

01:55.949 --> 02:00.854 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
House Republicans overnight
rebelled against
Paul Ryan and other leaders to
try and change

02:00.887 --> 02:02.389 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a House ethics panel.

02:02.422 --> 02:04.992 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Then, this morning, they
reversed course.

02:05.025 --> 02:10.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The proposed change was about
the independent
Office of Congressional Ethics,
or OCE, which

02:10.564 --> 02:12.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
reviews accusations.

02:12.499 --> 02:17.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It cannot punish members itself,
but it can
refer cases to the House Ethics
Committee.

02:17.971 --> 02:23.343 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The proposed revision would have
changed the
office's name to Complaint
Review and, more

02:23.377 --> 02:28.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
notably, would have stripped its
independence,
putting it under the control of
the House

02:28.482 --> 02:30.117 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Ethics Committee.

02:30.150 --> 02:33.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, some, like Iowa's Steve
King, were
dismayed that the measure was
pulled.

02:33.320 --> 02:34.554 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

02:34.588 --> 02:36.390 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEVE KING (R), Iowa: I think we
should have
gone forward.

02:36.423 --> 02:40.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I'm going to push for the
full disbandment
and abolishment of the OCE,
because they're

02:40.761 --> 02:42.529 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
based upon the wrong principles.

02:42.562 --> 02:47.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And no one should have to be
subjected to
public criticism that's
generated by anonymous

02:47.601 --> 02:49.369 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
accusers.

02:49.403 --> 02:51.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But more
Republicans, like
outgoing Ethics Committee
Chairman Charlie

02:51.738 --> 02:53.840 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Dent, said the change would have
been a mistake.

02:53.874 --> 02:55.442 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

02:55.475 --> 02:57.310 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLIE DENT (R), Pennsylvania:
I thought
it wasn't the right way to
proceed.

02:57.344 --> 03:00.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Perhaps no
coincidence, also
saying it was a mistake was
president-elect

03:00.747 --> 03:05.085 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trump, who asked on Twitter if
the change
should be a priority.

03:05.118 --> 03:09.389 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And House Democratic Leader
Nancy Pelosi slammed
Republicans, writing that the
move showed

03:09.423 --> 03:11.758 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
clear contempt for ethics.

03:11.792 --> 03:17.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It all led to rare tension on
what is usually
a happily bipartisan day with
members' families.

03:17.497 --> 03:22.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
During the roll call vote for
speaker, some
Democrats pointedly mentioned
the need for

03:22.169 --> 03:25.539 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
strong ethics, sparking boos
from Republicans.

03:25.572 --> 03:26.540 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BOOING)

03:26.573 --> 03:27.707 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:27.741 --> 03:29.076 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NANCY PELOSI (D-CA), House
Minority Leader:
Paul Ryan.

03:29.109 --> 03:30.844 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

03:30.877 --> 03:35.148 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: But now
beginning his first
full term as speaker, Paul Ryan
spoke not

03:35.182 --> 03:38.285 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to dissatisfied members, but to
dissatisfied
voters.

03:38.318 --> 03:40.087 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:40.120 --> 03:42.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker of the
House: So,
I want to say to the American
people, we hear

03:42.889 --> 03:44.257 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
you.

03:44.291 --> 03:46.626 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We will do right by you.

03:46.660 --> 03:48.295 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And we will deliver.

03:48.328 --> 03:51.965 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: In the Senate,
there was
less political theater, but more
signs of

03:51.998 --> 03:56.837 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
serious battles ahead, as new
Senate Democratic
Minority Leader Chuck Schumer
took on the

03:56.870 --> 04:01.641 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mantle of a key opposition voice
to president-elect-Trump
on Obamacare repeal.

04:01.675 --> 04:03.443 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:03.477 --> 04:05.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER (D-NY), Minority
Leader: Mr.
President-elect, what is your
plan to make

04:05.912 --> 04:10.617 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sure all Americans can get
affordable health
care?

04:10.650 --> 04:15.155 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: And a big day
today, but
an even bigger day tomorrow up
here, when

04:15.188 --> 04:20.660 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
President Obama and vice
president-elect Mike
Pence will both be here to talk
to their various

04:20.694 --> 04:22.696 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
parties about Obamacare -- Judy.

04:22.729 --> 04:28.101 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, Lisa, what
does this split
among Republicans over the
ethics office tell

04:28.135 --> 04:29.603 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
us about what's coming up ahead?

04:29.636 --> 04:33.373 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: I think it has
very serious
implications.

04:33.406 --> 04:37.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Republicans have long had
problems with issues
of rules and procedures, and
those continue.

04:37.811 --> 04:40.113 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There is a lot of unhappiness
with the conference.

04:40.147 --> 04:45.552 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think the bigger point
here is that
they remain a divided conference
on some serious

04:45.585 --> 04:47.320 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
issues.

04:47.354 --> 04:51.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And one big one is coming up in
which no one
in America has really the clear
direction

04:51.491 --> 04:53.760 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
yet, which is, how do you
replace Obamacare?

04:53.793 --> 04:59.132 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So the House caucus with the
Republicans is
having trouble with this Office
of Congressional

04:59.166 --> 05:02.536 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Ethics, which they have been
talking about
for years amongst themselves.

05:02.569 --> 05:08.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It raises questions about how
they will form
a plan to replace Obamacare in
the next year,

05:08.241 --> 05:10.043 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
if that is possible.

05:10.076 --> 05:13.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now, we heard
Speaker Ryan
say, among other things, "We
hear you," talking

05:13.380 --> 05:15.015 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to the voters.

05:15.048 --> 05:19.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, in fact, it was some voters
who were
weighing in today that had
something to do

05:19.386 --> 05:21.288 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
with this ethics outcome, didn't
it?

05:21.321 --> 05:23.156 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: It's such a
good point.

05:23.190 --> 05:27.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that what we're seeing
here is, while
voters are watching President
Trump, they're

05:27.694 --> 05:30.597 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
also very closely watching this
Congress.

05:30.630 --> 05:35.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's clear that voters don't
yet trust
Republicans here in Congress
fully, and they're

05:35.202 --> 05:36.670 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
watching carefully.

05:36.703 --> 05:40.540 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They reacted very quickly,
overwhelming phone
calls here at the Capitol.

05:40.574 --> 05:45.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I talked to a dozen members of
Congress who
said, Republicans and Democrats,
that their

05:45.412 --> 05:48.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
phone lines were clogged, and it
was about
that ethics change.

05:48.348 --> 05:53.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I talked to a House operator who
told me it
was just a mess, all those calls
coming in.

05:53.353 --> 05:56.723 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, Judy, what's amazing, that
change happened
late last night.

05:56.756 --> 05:58.959 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Voters got up and made those
phone calls right
away.

05:58.992 --> 06:03.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lisa, we also
heard a little
bit there from Chuck Schumer,
the incoming

06:04.030 --> 06:05.632 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Democratic leader in the Senate.

06:05.665 --> 06:08.401 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What is the opposition strategy
as of now?

06:08.435 --> 06:09.402 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Right.

06:09.436 --> 06:11.738 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Call him maybe the opposition in
chief.

06:11.771 --> 06:13.673 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Democrats have lot of recovery
to do.

06:13.707 --> 06:18.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's not clear who will be their
leading voice,
but right now Chuck Schumer
seems to be it.

06:18.678 --> 06:20.647 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm not sure what their strategy
is yet.

06:20.680 --> 06:25.418 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, they tried out one, which
is to question
how Donald Trump operates.

06:25.452 --> 06:29.956 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In his speech today, Chuck
assumer said it's
irresponsible the way that
Donald Trump makes

06:29.990 --> 06:30.924 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
decisions.

06:30.957 --> 06:31.925 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He pointed to his tweets.

06:31.958 --> 06:33.793 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's something we have heard
before, Judy.

06:33.827 --> 06:38.565 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But hearing that, I thought,
well, I'm not
sure that Trump voters, that
really hits where

06:38.598 --> 06:40.267 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
they are about Donald Trump.

06:40.300 --> 06:45.672 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I think we're going to see a
lot of different
attempts at answering Donald
Trump.

06:45.705 --> 06:49.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm not sure Democrats have
figured out how
to do it quite yet, but Chuck
Schumer is the

06:49.509 --> 06:51.411 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
man to watch.

06:51.444 --> 06:54.414 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In just a few
seconds, Lisa,
what's the word on Republican
plans on Obamacare?

06:54.447 --> 06:56.216 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Right.

06:56.249 --> 06:59.119 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Watch in the next couple of
days, especially
tomorrow morning, Judy, when
President Obama

06:59.152 --> 07:04.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
tries to rally his Democrat and
vice president-elect
Mike Pence tries to rally his
Republicans.

07:04.891 --> 07:08.595 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a several-step process
we're going to
be talking about for weeks.

07:08.628 --> 07:11.665 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And Lisa
Desjardins is going
to be right up there reporting.

07:11.698 --> 07:12.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thank you, Lisa.

07:12.699 --> 07:14.701 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: My pleasure.

07:14.734 --> 07:18.271 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
